query:

from performance.employer_employees employer_employees,
         performance.employer employer
where employer_employees.employer__id = employer.employer__id

SELECT *
FROM performance.employer_employees employer_employees  LEFT JOIN performance.employer employer ON (employer_employees.employer__id = employer.employer__id)

SELECT YEAR(createDate) FROM performance.employer GROUP BY YEAR(createDate)

query:
SELECT name FROM performance.employer
where createDate < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
SELECT name FROM performance.employer WHERE createDate < CURRENT_DATE
select UCASE(name) from performance.employer where UCASE(name) = 'FAY-FAY'
select LCASE(name) from  performance.employer where LCASE(name) =  'fay-fay'
select SUBSTRING(name,1,3) from performance.employer_employees where SUBSTRING(name,1,3) = 'Fay'
select LENGTH(name) from performance.employer where LENGTH(name)>0
select ROUND(salary, 2) from performance.employer_employees employer_employees where ROUND(salary,2)> 0
Select AVG(salary) from performance.employer_employees employer_employees group by type
test_name: SELECT AVG FROM GROUP BY TYPE

query: Select AVG(salary) from performance.employer_employees employer_employees group by type having  AVG(salary)>1
test_name: SELECT AVG FROM GROUP BY HAVING AVG

query: select Count(name) from performance.employer_employees group by type
select Count(name) from performance.employer_employees group by type having count(name)>1
test_name: SELECT COUNT FROM GROUP BY HAVING COUNT

query:
SELECT name, salary,
CASE
    WHEN salary > 10000 THEN 'Greater than 10000'
    WHEN salary = 10000 THEN 'Equal to 10000'
    ELSE 'Less than 10000'
END AS SalaryText
FROM performance.employer_employees

SELECT name, salary,type
FROM performance.employer_employees
ORDER BY
(CASE
    WHEN salary > 10000 THEN name
    ELSE type
END)

SELECT COUNT(*), AVG(employer_employees.salary), employer_employees.type, employer.name
FROM performance.employer_employees employer_employees,
     performance.employer employer
WHERE employer_employees.employer__id = employer.employer__id
  AND employer_employees.createDate < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
GROUP BY type
ORDER BY
(CASE
    WHEN salary > 10000 THEN name
    ELSE type
END)

SELECT COUNT(*), AVG(employer_employees.salary), employer_employees.type, employer.name
FROM performance.employer_employees employer_employees,
     performance.employer employer
WHERE employer_employees.employer__id = employer.employer__id
  AND employer_employees.createDate < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
GROUP BY type, employer.name
ORDER BY type

SELECT employer_employees.type, employer.name
FROM performance.employer_employees employer_employees,
     performance.employer employer
WHERE employer_employees.employer__id = employer.employer__id
  AND employer_employees.createDate < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
test_name: SELECT FROM TABLE, VIRTUAL WHERE ID and DATE

query:
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM performance.employer_employees employer_employees,
     performance.employer employer
WHERE employer_employees.employer__id = employer.employer__id
  AND employer_employees.createDate < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
GROUP BY type, employer.name
ORDER BY type
